  "title": "CYBER SECURITY CONSULTANT",
  "description": "<p><u>Key Responsibilities</u></p><ul><li>Monitor security alerts and events from SIEM, SOAR, EDR/XDR and other monitoring tools.</li><li>Correlate logs and alerts across diverse sources (firewalls, endpoints, servers, cloud, IoT/OT).</li><li>Perform triage of alerts to determine severity, scope and escalation path.</li><li>Document incidents and maintain detailed case records.</li><li>Escalate validated incidents to Tier 2/3 SOC Analysts with supporting evidence.</li><li>Support vulnerability monitoring and basic threat intelligence enrichment.</li><li>Participate in knowledge base updates and shift handovers.</li></ul><p><u>Qualifications</u></p><ul><li>Diploma/Bachelor’s degree in Information Security, Computer Science or related field</li><li>Certifications (advantageous but not required): CompTIA Security+, CySA+, Microsoft SC-200, Palo Alto</li><li>Understanding of network fundamentals, Windows/Linux OS basics and common security tools.</li><li>Strong willingness to learn and develop into advanced SOC roles.</li></ul>",
